  "title": "Release 5.1.20 (Build 36) #550d228",
  "body": "## Summary\n\n*   **NFC Task Tags** – Program physical NFC tags to trigger task actions (start/finish sessions) via deep links, and tap tags to open the app directly to relevant tasks with automatic tenant switching.\n*   **Approval & Acknowledgment Workflows** – New structured approval flows allow users to approve or reject tasks with electronic signatures and optional comments; acknowledgment status is now visible with timestamps and user attribution.\n*   **Enhanced Communication** – Chat messages with multiple images display in a 2×2 grid with overflow indicators; the full-screen viewer supports swipe navigation between images.\n*   **Privacy & Control** – GPS location capture for new tasks now defaults to **disabled** (opt-in via Settings).\n\n## Changes\n\n### NFC & Deep Linking\n*   **NFC Tag Programming** – Write task URLs to compatible NFC tags with tenant verification and status feedback (`NfcProgramTagScreen`).\n*   **NFC Tap Actions** – Execute task actions instantly by tapping programmed tags; supports automatic tenant context switching (`NfcTapScreen`).\n*   **Universal Links** – Added support for `*.whagons.com/nfc/*` domains to open NFC actions directly in-app on iOS and Android.\n\n### Task Management\n*   **Approval Workflows** – Tasks now support multi-step approvals with decision cards showing approver status, comments, and signature metadata in the activity feed.\n*   **Acknowledgment Tracking** – Redesigned acknowledgment section displays individual recipients with \"acknowledged by\" attribution and timestamps; visibility logic refined to show only when relevant.\n*   **Workspace Context** – Tasks viewed across multiple workspaces now correctly display active workspace context; template selection supports \"Everything\" mode with cross-workspace filtering.\n*   **Visual Indicators** – Task cards display color-coded badges for acknowledgment and approval states (e.g., \"Acknowledged\", \"Approved\", \"Rejected\").\n\n### Chat & Media\n*   **Gallery Grid** – Messages with 2–4 images render in a responsive 2×2 grid; overflow beyond 4 images shows a \"+N\" indicator.\n*   **Swipeable Viewer** – Full-screen media viewer supports horizontal swiping between images with pagination counters (e.g., \"2 / 5\").\n*   **Batched Uploads** – Multiple files uploaded simultaneously now send as a single combined message rather than separate messages.\n*   **Notification Formatting** – Push notifications display human-readable attachment labels (e.g., \"PDF attachment\") instead of raw markdown links; duplicate notifications filtered when tapping foreground messages.\n\n### Platform Experience\n*   **Keyboard Handling** – Improved bottom-sheet behavior in signature capture and rejection modals using `react-native-keyboard-controller` for consistent SafeArea handling on Android and iOS.\n*   **Web Compatibility** – Map views on web platforms now display a clear \"unavailable on web\" placeholder; full interactive maps remain available on iOS/Android.\n*   **Settings** – GPS location toggle default changed from enabled to disabled; users must explicitly opt-in to attach locations to new tasks.\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n*   **Build**: Version 5.1.20 (Build 36) – commit `550d228`\n*   **Release Pipeline**: Added Convex compatibility inventory checks before release generation; iOS release builds now auto-sync Xcode marketing version with GitHub releases.\n*   **Testing**: Introduced Playwright E2E smoke tests for mobile web (Pixel 7 profile).\n*   **Store Assets**: Automated generation of Play Store listing assets (512×512 icon, 1024×500 feature graphic) via `make play-listing-assets`.\n*   **Platform Split**: Refactored native-specific modules (`CallContext`, `MobileCallService`, `TaskNavigationMap`, `SpotsMapScreen`, Firebase services) to use `.native.tsx` extensions with web-compatible stubs.\n*   **Dependencies**: Added `react-native-nfc-manager` (v4.0.0-beta.7) with iOS associated domains and Android intent filters for Universal Links.",
